{"id":"haggith","term":"Haggith","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Festive; the dancer, a wife of David and the mother of Adonijah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 3:4\">2 Sam. 3:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 1:5\">1 Kings 1:5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:11\">11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:13\">2:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 3:2\">1 Chr. 3:2</a>), who, like Absalom, was famed for his beauty.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Samuel 3:4","1 Kings 1:5","Genesis 1:11","Genesis 2:13","1 Chronicles 3:2"]}